To do so, they go undercover as advertising executives "Stroganoff and Hopowitz" where Hoop gets caught up with trying to come up with a new ad campaign for Freshen Up Fabric Softeners. In the meantime, Rose has difficulty adjusting to prison where she gets on the wrong side of a Hispanic senior citizen gang.

table-0683-492.caption: Season 1: 2005-2007
data: When Pinky can't find her shoes, she goes to school with salami on her feet.
Pinky Dinky Doo and the Outer Space Fluffy Buns
Pinky and her family put too much baking powder in her fluffy buns and they lift her apartment up into outer space!
What's the name of my story?
When a famous tenor loses his voice, Mr. Guinea Pig and Tyler fill in at the opera.
Tyler catches a cold and is upset that he'll miss his trip to the Museum of Really Old Stuff, so Pinky tells him a story about her missing Show-and-Tell Day at school.
Pinky helps a grumpy alligator find a new home
Pinky attends a birthday party at a stuffy club where no laughing is allowed!
Tyler Dinky Doo and the Pirate Crew
When a pirate ship picks up Pinky and Tyler, they learn that even pirates have to clean up after themselves.
Pinky Dinky Doo and the Missing Dinosaurs
Pinky investigates some strange sounds at a museum and discovers a dinosaur rock band.
Pinky Dinky Doo and the Pizza Artist
Pinky helps Monsieur Guinea Pig paint the portrait of a friendly pizza vendor.
Pinky Dinky Doo and the Party Animals
Pinky wakes in the middle of the night to find a stuffed animal party happening in her living room.
Pinky runs into some problems when she uses her Tall-O-Meter to supersize herself!
Pinky Dinky Doo and the Cloud People
When Pinky encounters two clouds that are brother and sister, she helps them settle an argument over who will carry rain to Great Big City.
Tyler wants to be super scary when he goes trick-or-treating, but everybody just thinks he's cute.
Pinky and her class are in for a few surprises when their substitute teacher turns out to be a space alien.
Tyler Dinky Doo to the Rescue
When a giant ape captures Pinky, it's Tyler's turn to think big and rescue her.
Pinky shrinks herself to tiny proportions so she can avoid a new girl at school who seems mean.
Tyler misses all the fun when he won't stop playing his video game.
When Pinky forgets about cage cleaning day, Mr. Guinea Pig runs away from home.
Pinky and the Super Spaghetti Knot
Pinky and Mr. Guinea Pig are the best tightrope walkers at Great Big Circus—until their tightrope disappears!
The class picture could be a disaster when Pinky and her entire class have a bad hair day.
When Pinky doesn't want to be part of the soccer team, she finds she can still fit in by doing her own thing.
When Pinky's dragon friend keeps spilling his drinks, she makes him a sippy cup.
Tyler Dinky Doo and the Legend of Twigfoot
When Tyler refuses to take a bath, he becomes so dirty that he looks more like a monster than a little boy.
Pinky and the Big Rainy Day
Pinky has the worst day ever as one thing after the next goes wrong.
Pinky helps her stuffed penguin find some comfortable play clothes.
Pinky must get to the bottom of things when it snows in the middle of summer!
When Pinky leaves her instrument at home, she plays with Daphne's hair in the school concert.
Pinky is on the trail when someone mysteriously steals all the cheese from the cheese festival.
Try It, You'll Like It…Pretty Much
Pinky tries some very strange food when she judges a bake-off on another planet.
When Pinky duplicates herself in order to get her chores done, things get a bit out of control.
Daphne goes on a toy shopping spree and needs Pinky's help when she can't find her favorite doll Spendy Wendy in the mess.
There's a new superhero in Great Big City: "Boom! Sonic Boom!". Can reporter Pinky get the scoop?
A group of frogs catch Pinky's super leaping abilities and ask her to stay with them.
Pinky teaches her new pet guppy to swim in a big aquarium.
Pinky and Tyler are in for a few surprises when their new babysitter turns out to be a robot.
Pinky and Tyler follow clues in search of a missing sock!
Mr. Guinea Pig is invited to spend the night at his friend Harold the Hamster's house.
Pinky is in big trouble when she can't think of a talent for her class talent show.
Mr. Guinea Pig has lost his trumpet! To find it, he and Pinky retrace their steps.
Pinky and her family transform into superheroes when the president of Great Big City needs their help.
Pinky and the Ice Cream Babies
Things go wrong when Pinky opens an ice cream stand and hires two great big babies to help her out.
Mr. Guinea Pig and the Big Bone
Pinky builds a dinosaur skeleton out of Mr. Guinea Pig's bone collection.
Mr. Guinea Pig lets success go to his head when everybody likes a song he sings for Pinky.
Pinky has a mystery on her hands when everything in Great Big City turns pink.
Tyler must learn to ride a two-wheeler when Pinky needs his help in a bike race.
Tyler gets help from a magic Genie Pig when he doesn't want to go to bed.
When Mr. Guinea Pig can't wait for his loose tooth to fall out, Pinky takes him to visit the tooth fairy.
Pinky encounters a ladybug who is afraid to fly, and helps him get to a party on time.
Pinky and the Castle of Cards
When dancing dust bunnies approach, Pinky helps a king save his castle made out of cards.
Pinky is trying to get Daddy his special shirt in time for a big meeting. So she flies - on the shirt!

Then it occurred to the bhikkhuni Vajira: "Now who is this that recited the verse — a human being or a non-human being?" Then it occurred to her: "This is Mara the Evil One, who has recited the verse desiring to arouse fear, trepidation, and terror in me, desiring to make me fall away from concentration." Then the bhikkhuni Vajira, having understood, "This is Mara the Evil One," replied to him in verses: 35. "Why now do you assume 'a being'? Mara, have you grasped a view? This is a heap of sheer constructions: Here no being is found. 36. Just as, with an assemblage of parts, The word 'chariot' is used, So, when the aggregates are present, There's the convention 'a being.' 37. It's only suffering that comes to be, Suffering that stands and falls away. Nothing but suffering comes to be, Nothing but suffering ceases." Then Mara the Evil One, realizing, "The bhikkhuni Vajira knows me," sad and disappointed, disappeared right there.”

table-0683-493.caption: Season 2: 2008- 2009
data: When Pinky can't find the final piece in her 3D robot puzzle, Grandma Dinky Doo teaches her to think big.
When Pinky gets storyteller's block, she and Tyler make up a story about making up a story in Made-Up Story Land.
The Dinky Doos help an elephant remember his favorite song, and teach him not to be disruptive.
What's the Name of My Story?
Sir Guinea Pig the Brave Explorer conquers his fear of the dark when he goes to find the Magic Corn of Popping.
Some of Pinky's friends make fun of her for having bad breath. When she has an opportunity to make fun of Daffinee, Pinky learns to treat people the way she wants to be treated.
The Great Big Fancy Word Game
Pinky and her friends learn to collaborate when they enter a cooking contest in outer space.
When Speed Rocket Guinea Pig enters a big race, he learns to be persistent even when he's having some trouble.
When Nicholas puts on a magic show that goes wrong, Pinky helps him learn how to ask for help.
Jinkins the butler misses his family! Pinky and Daffinee help him make a video about his friends to send to his family.
When things go missing all around Great Big City, Pinky and the gang must find a giant pink gorilla and teach him to ask before taking something.
A Miggy Monster named Burpzilla has eaten the city's electrical plant! The Super Duper Doos must learn to concentrate so they can find out why Burpzilla is acting this way.
Pinky and her friends travel to Squeedorp Prime in search of a unique birthday present for Daffinee.
After Tyler accidentally breaks the Story Box, Pinky tells a story about a disaster in Great Big City and teaches him about doing the right thing and helping others.
Daffinee has trouble finding shoes for a fashion show when her "balloony feet" keep changing sizes.
